reaties were the first entered into by the united states government in new york city the first united states congress meets putting the constitution of the united states into effect france is divided into départements which cut across the former provinces in an attempt to dislodge regional loyalties based on noble ownership of land vermont is admitted as the th u s state a constitutional act is introduced by the british house of commons in london which envisages the separation of canada into lower canada quebec and upper canada ontario french troops conquer geertruidenberg netherlands the th amendment to the u s constitution was passed by the u s congress in the first ever peaceful transfer of power between elected leaders in modern times john adams is sworn in as president of the united states succeeding george washington the battle of vinegar hill colony of new south wales australia when irish convicts some of whom had been involved in ireland s battle of vinegar hill in led the colony s only significant convict uprising russian troops fighting the army of napoleon reach berlin in germany and the french garrison evacuate the city without a fight americans defeat the british at the battle of longwoods between london and thamesville near present day wardsville ontario the national institution for the preservation of life from shipwreck was founded in the united kingdom later to be renamed the royal national lifeboat institution in chicago becomes incorporated as a city carlo alberto di savoia signs the statuto albertino that will later represent the first constitution of the regno d italia first national flag of the confederate states of america the stars and bars adopted third and last national flag of the confederate states of america adopted pyotr ilyich tchaikovsky s ballet swan lake premiers at the bolshoi theatre in moscow britain s first electric trams run in east london gottlieb daimler unveils his first automobile which he test runs in esslingen and cannsta